<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,286,467]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,330,363,389]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName box="[367,691,364,390]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Tubularia">
<emphasis box="[367,508,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Monotagma</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[576,691,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Tubularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises 17 species. It is characterized by having fruits with a one-layered mesocarp with unsclerified cells, and tubular arils with laterally united lobes. These features are apomorphic for this section (
<bibRefCitation author="Hagberg, M." box="[487,675,441,467]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref20101" refString="Hagberg, M. (1990 b) The genus Monotagma (Marantaceae). Unpublished Ph. D. dissertation, Department of Systematic Botany, University of Gothenburg, 90 pp." type="book" year="1990">Hagberg 1990b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
